reviews.review: Really enjoyable film, great character development and most importantly you need to realise that they managed to fix every mess the last Jedi made which was a tough task
The storyline had a couple surprises, not epic but good. Adam Driver was really good, But Daisy Ridley carried the movie and just watching Rey develop and kick some serious a is worth going to see!
Good movie and better than the last 2 episodes
I really enjoyed the film, it brought me back to my childhood and kept the spirit of Star Wars alive!
Great movie!  Completed the trilogy for me !!! Great theater and comfortable seats !!

Extremely fan servicy (which is fine, I am a fan) but it took no risks and was super frenetic, especially in the first 3rd. It settled in and became better as it went on once it got past the "video game" phase of go to planet X, complete quest Y

Great Effects! Best battles of any Star Wars movie. Funny, moving everything a star wars movie should be. There were a couple hokey moments that I could have done without but people need to lighten up. Everyone should see it.

Well. That's over. 40 years in the making. And did Disney/Abrams manage to finish in beauty as expected? Do I go out from the cinema with the joy of my childhood?
No.
Sadly this episode did not mark me. And I feel angry to be disappointed. But at the same time, it follows a form of logic since Disney decided to follow up Lucas' universe.... without Lucas.
Probably the main and only problem of those sequels. The soul of Star Wars is not there. Abrams has no option but to renew what was done before. 40 years ago. With little creativity. The mind of Lucas being absent, Abram do his best to please us, bringing few new characters, good actors, great special effects, and getting rid of The Last Jedi.. .. But it is not enough for us to praise this work. Something is missing and the story is too messy.
I am glad it is over. I will probably give it a second chance on Bluray, but for now... I will, l like many, try to digest what I just saw...
This movie deserves a lot of credit for giving the fans service, lots of nostalgia, all while correctimg course from TLJ screw ups and closing out the series as best possible. Major Kudos to J.J.
